{
  "stem": "2916.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The part of the plane that I was manufacturing, by the way, was a very sensitive and a very, supposedly, highly intelligent work.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I had to put together, on a machine, you know, solder together pieces that, when it was finished, it had a small equipment, a small part of an equipment, which measured the distance of the bomb and the direction of the bomb on the plane.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was built into the mechanism of-- the bombing mechanism.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And so this was the work we did, 12-hour shifts, one week by day, and one week by night.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was very, very hard labor to work for 12 hours with minimum food.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But it wasn't Auschwitz, and it wasn't Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And luckily, we were there all winter long till the end of March 1945, which was a very fortunate thing because only two people were lost to us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "One girl who, for some reason, attempted to escape and she was taken to the Dachau to be executed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And another woman who discovered in Auschwitz that she's pregnant.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And she was taken away to the Dachau when she was already advanced in her pregnancy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we knew that we lost these two.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So instead of 500, we were 498 women when we were evacuated into Dachau at the end of March 1945.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Can you just tell us how--",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
